ICD-10-CM (International Classification of Diseases, 10th Revision, Clinical
Modification) is produced by the U.S. National Center for Health Statistics
(NCHS) and the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services (CMS), and is in the
public domain in the United States.

- The bundled code descriptions are sourced from the CMS ICD-10-CM release and
  the NIH Clinical Tables Search Service (clinicaltables.nlm.nih.gov), both
  public-domain U.S. government data.
- The full code set is generated into data/icd10cm-codes.json via
  scripts/build-data.mjs (see README).

icdwise validates and describes codes; it is not medical advice and does not
determine billability, coverage, or clinical appropriateness.
